a sudden rash of illness affecting 
hundreds of university of north dakota students who ate at a school 
cafeteria has been blamed on food poisoning university officials 
said 
more than 220 students had been treated with antibiotics at the 
schools student health services as of friday university spokesman 
peter johnson said two diabetic students were hospitalized as a 
precaution johnson said 
all of the students apparently had eaten recently at the 
wilkerson hall cafeteria school officials said the cafeteria 
serves a university complex of five residence halls which house 
about 1500 students 
dr john swenson director of student health services said food 
poisoning was the most likely cause of the illnesses which 
included stomach cramps diarrhea and vomiting 
