<TEXT>
the chairman of the nuclear regulatory 
commission says the idled seabrook nh reactor will not get a 
lowpower operating license until regulators are convinced the 
plants owners are financially stable 
but seabrook officials buoyed by a commission vote friday that 
removed the only other regulatory obstacle to gaining the license 
said they will begin immediately preparing the reactor for 
lowpower testing in anticipation of a license 
the nrc voted 40 for a rules clarification that will allow 
nuclear plants to receive lowpower permits without an emergency 
siren system in place to alert neighbors within 10 miles of the 
reactors of an atomic emergency 
commission regulations say financial qualification should not be 
a consideration for a lowpower license but nrc chairman lando w 
