quality inns international inc must stop using 
the name mcsleep inns for its economy hotels because the public 
would believe the hotels are owned by the fastfood giant 
mcdonalds corp a judge ruled friday 
us district judge paul niemeyer said the use of the prefix 
mc is a deliberate attempt to benefit by the good will and 
reputation of mcdonalds 
he granted mcdonalds a permanent injuction and gave quality 
inns 30 days to comply with the injunction 
the company immediately responded to the injunction by changing 
the name of their new hotel chain to sleep inns which will 
offer a nights lodging for 20 to 29 the first two sleep 
inns will break ground next week in nova scotia canada and 
salisbury nc the company said 
the last thing we wanted for our lodging product is to be 
confused with some hamburger chain said gerald petitt executive 
vice president and chief operating officer for quality inns 
well change the name to eliminate any chance of anyone being 
confused 
last september quality inns based in silver spring announced 
the new chain of economy hotels to be marketed under the name 
mcsleep inns 
three days later mcdonalds demanded that the name not be used 
after repeated warnings from mcdonalds quality inns filed suit 
against the hamburger chain asking the court to declare that 
mcsleep does not infringe on the chains trademark quality 
inns said the mcsleep name was selected because it connotes a 
