<TEXT>
the us bond market which has proven 
attractive in recent years for japanese investors showed it can be 
gracious on those rare occasions when it gets a call from a 
borrower affiliated with a japanese company 
the market provided a warm reception this past week for a 200 
million issue of threeyear notes from toyota motor credit corp 
the us finance subsidiary of the japanese automaker toyota motor 
corp 
the notes sold in denominations of 1000 were priced to yield 
8826 percent or a slim 38hundredths of a percentage point more 
than treasury securities with a similar maturity 
we were very pleased it went very well and sold out within 
one hour said wolfgang jahn vice president for toyota motor 
credit in torrance calif 
he said while the company has no specific plans for additional 
offerings he said he expects to be back 
according to the research firm securities data co the sale was 
the first straight public debt offering in the united states in 10 
