toyota motor credit makes loans to us toyota dealers and their 
customers 
it has grown rapidly over the past three years and counts over 
3 billion in accounts receivable on its books according to jahn 
jahn said the company started out raising money in the 
euromarkets because they offered ready access and cheaper rates 
initially than the us markets 
but jahn said as the companys growth accelerated it found it 
needed to return to the euromarket more frequently 
over the past three years he said toyota motor credit raised 2 
billion in 16 separate offerings and that in recent months found 
itself going back to the market with new offerings every six to 
eight months 
we realized that we couldnt raise all our funds in europe 
he said it was time for us to enter the us market 
lerner said merrill lynch worked for nine months to come up with 
documents acceptable to the company and the sec he said a 
firsttime issuer could get into the euromarkets on the other 
hand in two weeks 
nonetheless jahn said toyota motor credit wanted to make sure 
we have the capability of going into the us market to 
accommodate the companys expected growth 
it is the deepest and most liquid debt market in the world 
added lloyd misteli assistant treasurer at toyota motor credit 
lerner said he expects toyota motor credit will become one of 
the most active issuers in the us debt markets within two years 
joining a group that included the financing arms of the big three 
us automakers 
